summary: I was reading about Aegon III and noticed there's a lot similarities between them(Aegon saw his dragon killed, Sansa saw her...
question: I was reading about Aegon III and noticed there's a lot similarities between them(Aegon saw his dragon killed, Sansa saw her direwolf killed,both of them saw one of their parents executed, both were forced to marry a member of the family that killed said parent, both mistakenly believed all their full-blooded siblings had died, ect.). Do you think this is just a coincidence or might it be a hint towards Sansa's future?
answer:
I don’t believe GRRM writes characters in order to provide roadmaps to the futures of other characters, no. In this particular case, Sansa’s story is light on Targaryen associations. There’s no link between her and Aegon III except misfortune.

It’s also pretty unfortunate, but there’s so much trauma going around in Westeros that if you start listing the bad stuff that happens to characters, you’re going to get some overlap in the lists.
